<!-- ============ ARTICLE ============ -->
<section class="sec" style="padding-top:40px">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="post-wrap post-body reveal">
<p>Brands promote webinars to prospects with video by using short teaser clips, countdown videos, and post-event highlight reels to build anticipation and keep the momentum going after the session ends. A teaser gives prospects a preview of the speakers and topics so they know exactly why the webinar is worth their time, while countdown and follow-up videos extend that reach before and after the live event. Together, these formats turn a single webinar into an ongoing stream of touchpoints with your audience.</p>
<h2>Why Video Promotes Webinar Attendance</h2>
<p>A short teaser video that gives a sneak peek of an upcoming webinar is far more effective at scrolling feeds than a plain text announcement. These videos highlight key speakers or the topics that will be discussed, giving prospects a concrete reason to register rather than a vague promise of value.</p>
<h3>What Makes a Great Webinar Teaser Video?</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Highlighting speakers:</strong> Featuring the experts who will present builds credibility — recognisable names and faces increase sign-up rates.</li>
<li><strong>Exciting topics:</strong> A glimpse of the subjects being covered helps prospects judge relevance to their own needs before committing their time.</li>
<li><strong>Engaging visuals:</strong> Strong pacing, clean graphics, and music keep the teaser watchable in a crowded feed.</li>
</ul>
<p>A well-produced <a href={p("services/brand-video")}>brand video</a> approach to these teasers ensures they still feel consistent with the rest of your marketing, even though they're built for a single event.</p>
<h2>Effective Webinar Promotion Formats</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Countdown videos:</strong> These create urgency by reminding prospects how little time remains to register.</li>
<li><strong>Follow-up clips:</strong> Shared after the webinar, these highlight key takeaways for people who missed it — and give them a reason to register for the next one.</li>
</ul>
<p>Distributing these clips through <a href={p("services/social-media-video")}>social media video</a> extends their reach well beyond your existing email list, putting the webinar in front of prospects who haven't engaged with your brand yet.</p>
<h2>Building a Full Webinar Video Funnel</h2>
<p>The most effective webinar campaigns don't rely on a single video. A teaser drives initial registrations, a countdown video re-engages people who signed up but haven't set a reminder, and a follow-up highlight reel captures value for everyone who didn't attend live. Treating these as one connected sequence — rather than isolated assets — keeps your webinar visible across the full promotion window, not just in the days immediately before it airs.</p>
<h2>Ready to Elevate Your Brand?</h2>
<p>At Viven, we specialize in creating promotional webinar videos that increase registrations and attract high-quality leads, whether you need a teaser, a countdown, or follow-up clips. This kind of ongoing engagement pairs well with a broader strategy for <a href={p("blog/how-video-campaigns-drive-event-attendance-and-engagement")}>driving event attendance</a> across your marketing calendar.</p>
<p><a href={p("contact")}>Contact Viven to plan the video content for your next webinar.</a></p>
